    "content": "## Idea\n- compare all (odd,even) indexed pairs of adjacent elements\n- if a pair is in the wrong order, switch elements\n- then alternate between (odd,even) and (even,odd) pairs\n\n## Implementation\n```java\npublic class OddEvenSort{\n    public static void sort(int[] arr){\n\t\tif(arr==null || arr.length<=1){\n\t\t\treturn;\n\t\t}\n\t\tboolean sorted = false;\n\t\tint len = arr.length;\n\t\twhile(!sorted){\n\t\t\tsorted = true;\n\t\t\t//(odd,even) pairs\n\t\t\tfor(int i=1; i<len-1; i+=2){\n                if(arr[i] > arr[i+1]){\n                \tswap(arr,i,i+1);\n                \tsorted = false;\n                } \n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t//(even,odd) pairs\n\t\t\tfor(int i=0; i<len-1; i+=2){\n\t\t\t\tif(arr[i] > arr[i+1]){\n\t\t\t\t\tswap(arr,i,i+1);\n\t\t\t\t\tsorted = false;\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tpublic static void swap(int[] arr, int i, int j){\n\t\tint temp = arr[i];\n\t\tarr[i] = arr[j];\n\t\tarr[j] = temp;\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n## Runtime\n- Time O(n^2)\n- Space O(1)\n\n## Reference\n- [Odd Even Sort / Brick Sort](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/odd-even-sort-brick-sort/)"
